  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (a44159a 2023-01-03T00:04:41.810446Z)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nforge build\n\n### Operating System\n\nmacOS (Apple Silicon)\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nI'm in China.\r\nWhen I run `forge build` it will shows a connection refused error. Looks like the url has been banned in China. But I used proxy and can visit the url by using chrome. \r\n<img width=\"946\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/46948182/210958509-7dda1e12-6973-4c10-b6cc-c0807cbaa2ba.png\">\r\n\r\nAnd another connection error is `unexpected end of file`.\r\n<img width=\"944\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/46948182/210958755-7b136f6e-3600-48b6-a1b1-faaa9044193e.png\">\r\n\r\nIf I use hardhat, I could add proxy codes in `hardhat.config` like this to solve:\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/46948182/210959039-f5f2e36d-5d31-4b56-9db8-0dea480bb117.png)\r\n\r\nIt is always hard to dev in China, but there are lots of blockchain developers in China who love foundry, hoping you could solve this. Thank you! 😘",
